        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43277",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think, there is no need, because you can use \"overloading\":\r\n{code}\r\n$element->size = 10;\r\n$element->class = 'notice';\r\n{code}\r\n[http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/apidoc\/core\/Zend_Form\/Element\/Zend_Form_Element.html#__set]\r\n\r\nThere are too many attributes and HTML5 is coming!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-11-23T10:03:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-11-23T10:07:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43295",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thadafinser",
                        "name": "thadafinser",
                        "displayName": "Martin Keckeis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sure you can also use this method.\r\nBut exactly this is my point.\r\n\r\nWhen you are new to the ZF you have first to crawl the documentation or the source code to find out, that this is possible.\r\nIf there are clear methods, the questions go away, because you see what you can do (and not intend or read what it is possible).\r\n\r\nMaybe the definition from \"Ease the learning curve\" should be clear defined befor implmenting this feature.\r\n\r\nThe argument that there are \"too many\" attributes don't count in my oppinion:\r\nhttp:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/html401\/interact\/forms.html#h-17.6\r\n\r\nFor select, optgroup, option there are only 7 additional attributes (not counting \"name\").\r\n\r\n\r\nHTML5 is still not completely defined, and much applications will still have HTMl4 several years (IE6-IE8 will not support it!).\r\nFurther HTML5 form elements are not complete different from HTML4.\r\n\r\nMaybe thinking about this feature multiple times, but also from different view ports!\r\n\r\n\r\nI think above in my listing there are some very good arguments for this feature.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thadafinser",
                        "name": "thadafinser",
                        "displayName": "Martin Keckeis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-11-23T23:11:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-11-23T23:11:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43296",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mjh_ca",
                        "name": "mjh_ca",
                        "displayName": "Marc Hodgins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Martin: How would you approach compatibility among various versions of HTML?  Some attributes are deprecated, others added.. So depending on the doctype, you'd have setter functions for attributes that are not valid under that doctype.  In this sense, adding these functions would be less clear rather than more clear -- i.e. a user would call a set function, assuming it is taking care of generating valid HTML, but then the element would output invalid HTML...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mjh_ca",
                        "name": "mjh_ca",
                        "displayName": "Marc Hodgins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-11-23T23:50:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-11-23T23:50:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43300",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Martin\r\n??But exactly this is my point.??\r\nI understand completely what you want.\r\n\r\n??When you are new to the ZF you have first to crawl the documentation or the source code to find out, that this is possible. If there are clear methods, the questions go away, because you see what you can do (and not intend or read what it is possible).??\r\nThis is also a problem of the documentation (Reference guide and API). The review of documentation is a topic for version 2.\r\nCurrently, the description is just too poor and too short: (API)\r\n\r\n{quote}\r\n__set\r\nOverloading: set object property\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\n[http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/apidoc\/1.11\/Zend_Form\/Element\/Zend_Form_Element.html#__set]\r\n\r\n??Further HTML5 form elements are not complete different from HTML4.??\r\nTrue, but it adds even more attributes.\r\n\r\n??I think above in my listing there are some very good arguments for this feature.??\r\nRight, but I also agree with Marc.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-11-24T02:23:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-11-24T02:24:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43313",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thadafinser",
                        "name": "thadafinser",
                        "displayName": "Martin Keckeis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Marc:\r\nIt's already implmented in ZF.\r\nThe doctype comes in play how the tags get closed:\r\nhttp:\/\/akrabat.com\/zend-framework\/top-tip-xhtml-with-zend-form-elements\/\r\n\r\nCurrently you can say HTML4 form elements are the standard (with the difference of closing in XHTML)\r\n\r\nAnyway it will be a problem with the gap from HTML4 to HTML5.\r\nThere are a lot different elements or attributes - http:\/\/diveintohtml5.org\/forms.html\r\n\r\nSupporting both will sure be necessary. How will it be done there?\r\nIf there is a solution, there will also be a solution for this problem.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thadafinser",
                        "name": "thadafinser",
                        "displayName": "Martin Keckeis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-11-24T10:07:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-11-24T10:07:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44094",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=richardtuin",
                        "name": "richardtuin",
                        "displayName": "Richard Tuin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Element attributes other than name and value are in fact just metadata, as defined in the [Zend\\Form|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFDEV2\/Zend_Form+2.0#Zend_Form2.0-Makethemetadata%2Fbehaviorseparationexplicit] proposals (ZF 2.0).\r\n\r\nIn my opinion metadata should be flexible and undefined.\r\nMaking seperate setter\/getter methods for attributes defined in web standards would suggest separation from the underlying data structure.\r\nMaking this just a matter of good documentation.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=richardtuin",
                        "name": "richardtuin",
                        "displayName": "Richard Tuin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-20T13:56:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-20T13:56:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51047",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=frosch",
                        "name": "frosch",
                        "displayName": "Frank Br\u00fcckner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Have a look at the version 2 and the complete new [Zend\\Form component|https:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/zf2\/blob\/master\/library\/Zend\/Form].",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=frosch",
